  "Hartung-Knapp-Sidik-Jonkman adjustment uses t-distribution instead of normal, providing more accurate confidence intervals especially with few studies. Recommended when k less than 10.": "Hartung-Knapp-Sidik-Jonkman adjustment uses t-distribution instead of normal, providing more accurate confidence intervals especially with few studies. Recommended when k less than 10.",
  "Not necessarily. Asymmetry can be due to true heterogeneity, study quality differences, or chance (especially with few studies). Combine with statistical tests and consider the context.": "Not necessarily. Asymmetry can be due to true heterogeneity, study quality differences, or chance (especially with few studies). Combine with statistical tests and consider the context.",
